# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   Reference: https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in git.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if lock is not desired, it can be added here.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock is generally tracked, but can be excluded.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock is generally tracked, but can be excluded.
#.pdm.toml
#.pdm-plugins/
#pdm.lock

